title: Girls Cross Country Roundup: Bears seventh
text:
Girls Cross Country Roundup: Bears seventh 11:38 p.m. EDT October 10, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Fostoria Booster Invitational 
Gibsonburg placed seventh and Old Fort 11th Saturday in the girls Black Division race at the Fostoria Booster Invitational. Leading Gibsonburg were Samantha deAnda (16th, 21:26.75), Jasmine Stein (24th, 21:54.98), Jenna Lewandowski (43rd, 23:34.58), Heidi Rakay (52nd, 24:12.55) and Maria Ruggiero (62nd, 24:39.69). 
Leading Old Fort were Makinsey Black (74th, 25:38.72), Maddi Spencer (82nd, 26:32.64), Nikki Fry (83rd, 26:35.33), Alyssa Pence (110th, 30:57.89) and Cheyenne Halbeisen (112th, 31:32.78). 
St. Joseph had four runners: Brooke Foster (18th, 21:34.64), Lexie Steinberger (21st, 21:50.67), Chloe Liebold (34th, 23:08.39) and Sarah Molyet (39th, 23:25.30). 
In the girls Red Division race, Clyde placed sixth, Woodmore eighth and Oak Harbor ninth. Leading Clyde were Olivia Hammons (fifth, 20:15.68), Hayley Robinett (10th, 20:47.26), Mackenzie Baker (38th, 22:17.70), Carlie Magers (47th, 22:40.22) and Kim Rohrbach (55th, 23:00.47). 
Leading Woodmore were Courtney Burner (second, 19:44.01), Samantha Sedlmeier (29th, 21:55.25), Jordan Grzegorczyk (50th, 22:45.56), Amber Zarella (53rd, 22:56.43) and Jessica Sotak (77th, 23:46.12). 
Pacing Oak Harbor were Makayla Wagner (20th, 21:24.87), Alyssa Fuller (46th, 22:28.55), Taylor Dunn (48th, 22:44.79) and Karissa Garza (64th, 23:20.37). 
Rocket Invitational 
Lakota girls placed 13th in the Rocket Invitational at Anna Saturday. Leading Lakota were Brooke Shank (57th, 22:01.5), Anna Klotz (74th, 22:44.2), Rachel Miller (99th, 23:19.2), Tain Cozette (103rd, 23:32.2) and Sara Jay (134th, 24:41.7).
